#Hashing

Hashing is the process of converting a key 
into a numeric value (hash code) so data can be stored and found quickly.


Imagine every student gets a locker number.

Instead of checking every locker, you directly go to the assigned locker.

Hashing works the same way.

Why do we need it?

To avoid searching every stored element.

Important Points

* Produces a hash code
* Helps in fast lookup
* Used by HashMap

Real-world Examples

* Dictionary
* Library catalog
* User session lookup

Memory Trick

Hashing = Finding the correct locker

60-Second Revision

* Key → Hash Code
* Faster searching
